    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Carroll County was formed in 1842 from Grayson County.  Part of Patrick County was added in 1856.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Carroll County (Va.) Various Court Records, 1888-1899.
Consists of an execution from the court case, Commonwealth vs. Jane Stonerman, 1888; a search warrant for the house of  Rebecca Kelly, in response to a complaint of theft from Ira Norvell, 1896; a receipt pertaining to the court case Lancheiner and Sons vs. Owens, 1898; a receipt from P.T. Beamer, Trustee, 1890; and a subpoena for the testimony of Henry Carter on behalf of George Davis in the court case Commonwealth vs. George Davis, 1899.</p>
    </scopecontent>
